CatDescriptText: Mrs. Adeline Harris, 646 Herron Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 4, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Do you believe that Negro communities actually choose their leaders or do they accept the leadership, which 'the powers-that-be' select and 'hand' to them?" answer reads: "No, I don't think they choose their own leaders. I think they accept those given to them."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Adeline Harris wearing one earring in right ear, light colored striped blouse, and basket weave patterned skirt, leaning against desk with books, in interior with light colored walls
